data.title: Jack Dempsey for Trustee
data.text: Born in Detroit in 1952, Jack received his undergrad degree in political science with high honors from Michigan State University and his law degree with honors from George Washington University, where he was an editor on the law review. While in college and law school he served on staff for Congressman Garry Brown (R-Schoolcraft). He served as Michigan Assistant Attorney General from 1980-84. He rose to General Counsel at Michigan Bell Telephone Company between 1984-1998. He taught adjunct classes at Michigan State University in finance and policy. Since 1998 he has been a partner in the Lansing and Ann Arbor offices of Dickinson Wright PLLC, one of Michiganâ€™s oldest and most prestigious law firms. He and Suzzanne have been married for 42 years.
